{"note":"from fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\nfrom fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport os\n\napp = FastAPI(title=\"DFS Correlation API\")\n\napp.add_middleware(\n    CORSMiddleware,\n    allow_origins=[\"*\"],\n    allow_credentials=True,\n    allow_methods=[\"*\"],\n    allow_headers=[\"*\"],\n)\n\n@app.get(\"\/\")\nasync def root():\n    return {\n        \"status\": \"DFS Correlation Engine - Live on Railway\",\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n        \"version\": \"1.0\"\n    }\n\n@app.get(\"\/api\/recommendations\")\nasync def get_recommendations(risk_level: str = \"balanced\", bankroll: int = 20000):\n    try:\n        recommendations = [\n            {\n                \"id\": 1,\n                \"sport\": \"NFL\",\n                \"platform\": \"PrizePicks\",\n                \"title\": \"Mahomes\/Kelce Stack\",\n                \"picks\": [\n                    {\"player\": \"Patrick Mahomes\", \"stat\": \"Passing Yards\", \"line\": 275.5, \"direction\": \"OVER\"},\n                    {\"player\": \"Travis Kelce\", \"stat\": \"Receiving Yards\", \"line\": 65.5, \"direction\": \"OVER\"}\n                ],\n                \"correlation\": 0.68,\n                \"winProbability\": 0.42,\n                \"expectedValue\": 26.00,\n                \"roi\": 26.0,\n                \"entrySizeRecommended\": 150,\n                \"confidence\": 95,\n                \"reasoning\": \"Strong QB-TE correlation. When Mahomes exceeds 275 yards, Kelce hits 78% of the time.\",\n                \"tier\": \"S-Tier\"\n            }\n        ]\n        \n        return {\n            \"success\": True,\n            \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n            \"recommendations\": recommendations\n        }\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=str(e))\n\n@app.get(\"\/api\/health\")\nasync def health_check():\n    return {\"status\": \"healthy\", \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat()}\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    import uvicorn\n    port = int(os.environ.get(\"PORT\", 8000))\n    uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=port)\n```\n\n3. **Paste it** into Notepad\/TextEdit\n\n4. **Save the file:**\n   - Click File â†’ Save As\n   - Navigate to your `dfs-engine` folder\n   - **File name**: `main.py` (exactly like that, including the `.py`)\n   - **Save as type** (Windows): Select \"All Files\" (not .txt!)\n   - Click Save\n\n### Option 2: Using VS Code (If you have it)\n\n1. Open VS Code\n2. Open your `dfs-engine` folder\n3. Click \"New File\"\n4. Name it `main.py`\n5. Paste the code above\n6. Save (Ctrl+S or Cmd+S)\n\n---\n\n## Now create the other 2 files the same way:\n\n### File 2: `requirements.txt`\n\nCopy this (4 lines):\n```\nfastapi==0.109.0\nuvicorn[standard]==0.27.0\npython-multipart==0.0.6\npydantic==2.5.3\n```\n\nSave as `requirements.txt` in your `dfs-engine` folder\n\n### File 3: `Procfile` (no extension!)\n\nCopy this (1 line):\n```\nweb: uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT","bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":0}